House Resolution 752
By: Representatives Barnes of the 86th, Glaize of the 67th, Burnough of the 77th, Mitchell of
the 88th, Schofield of the 63rd, and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the Joint Study Committee on Cosmetology and Barbering Education; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the professions of cosmetology and barbering and schools for cosmetology and
4 barbering are important to the growth and success of Georgia's economy; and
5 WHEREAS, accredited private schools of cosmetology, schools of hair design, schools of
6 esthetics, schools of nail care, and schools of barbering in this state provide high quality
7 education and training for their students so they can become licensed professionals,
8 educators, and entrepreneurs; and
9 WHEREAS, such schools and their students do not receive the same opportunities to
10 participate in workforce development programs or to obtain state funded scholarships, loans,
11 and grants that may be available for comparable programs within the Technical College
12 System of Georgia or for private postsecondary institutions; and
13 WHEREAS, state support for such schools and their students would contribute to the
14 education and development of Georgia's workforce and to the growth and success of
15 Georgia's economy.
