16 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF
17 GEORGIA:
18 (1) Creation of joint study committee. There is created the Joint Study Committee on
19 Cosmetology and Barbering Education.
20 (2) Members and officers.
21 (A) The committee shall be composed of 12 members.
22 (B) The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall appoint five members of the
23 House of Representatives as members of the committee and shall designate one of such
24 members as cochairperson. The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall also
25 appoint one additional nonlegislative member with experience in cosmetology and
26 barbering education.
27 (C) The President of the Senate shall appoint five members of the Senate as members
28 of the committee and shall designate one of such members as cochairperson. The
29 President of the Senate shall also appoint one additional nonlegislative member with
30 experience in cosmetology and barbering education.
31 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
32 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
33 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
34 (4) Meetings. The cochairpersons shall call all meetings of the committee. The
35 committee may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem
36 necessary or convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform
37 its duties, and accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
38 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
39 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
40 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
41 (B) Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative members,
42 or state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the committee,
