43 but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the performance of their
44 duties as members of the committee in the same manner as they are reimbursed for
45 expenses in their capacities as state officials or employees.
46 (C) Members of the committee who are not legislators, state officials, or state
47 employees shall receive a daily expense allowance in an amount the same as that
48 specified in subsection (b) of Code Section 45-7-21 of the Official Code of Georgia
49 Annotated, as well as the mileage or transportation allowance authorized for state
50 employees.
51 (D) The allowances and expenses authorized by this resolution shall not be received
52 by any member of the committee for more than five days unless additional days are
53 authorized. Funds necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come
54 from funds appropriated to the House of Representatives and Senate; except that funds
55 for the reimbursement of the expenses of state officials, other than legislative members,
56 and state employees shall come from funds appropriated to or otherwise available to
57 their respective agencies.
58 (6) Report.
59 (A) In the event the committee adopts any specific findings or recommendations that
60 include suggestions for proposed legislation, the cochairpersons shall file a report of the
61 same prior to the date of abolishment specified in this resolution, subject to
62 subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
63 (B) In the event the committee adopts a report that does not include suggestions for
64 proposed legislation, the cochairpersons shall file the report, subject to subparagraph
65 (C) of this paragraph.
66 (C) No report shall be filed unless the same has been approved prior to the date of
67 abolishment specified in this resolution by majority vote of a quorum of the committee.
68 A report so approved shall be signed by the cochairpersons of the committee and filed
69 with the Clerk of the House of Representatives and the Secretary of the Senate.
